WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.801 --> 00:00:10.217
Who would you say is the father?

2
00:00:10.634 --> 00:00:11.718
You.

3
00:00:12.759 --> 00:00:15.259
I'm going to put a prince
in your belly.

4
00:00:17.550 --> 00:00:21.009
Our queen has a keen sense
of poetic justice.

5
00:00:21.091 --> 00:00:22.509
What would she do for the man

6
00:00:22.593 --> 00:00:24.718
who rids her
of her treasonous brothers?

7
00:00:25.593 --> 00:00:28.091
My name...
my real name...

8
00:00:28.760 --> 00:00:30.216
is Aegon Targaryen.

9
00:00:30.885 --> 00:00:31.966
It's true. Dany.

10
00:00:32.468 --> 00:00:33.634
If it were true...

11
00:00:34.259 --> 00:00:35.738
you'd have a claim
to the Iron Throne.

12
00:00:36.426 --> 00:00:38.426
She doesn't like
your queen. does she?

13
00:00:38.843 --> 00:00:40.468
She's defending our family.

14
00:00:40.759 --> 00:00:42.134
I'm her family. too.

15
00:00:43.676 --> 00:00:44.884
Don't forget that.

16
00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:52.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

17
00:05:26.966 --> 00:05:30.216
We're here to say goodbye
to our brothers and sisters.

18
00:05:31.216 --> 00:05:33.550
To our fathers and mothers.

19
00:05:35.384 --> 00:05:36.509
To our friends.

20
00:05:38.134 --> 00:05:39.966
Our fellow men and women

21
00:05:40.050 --> 00:05:42.675
who set aside
their differences...

22
00:05:44.091 --> 00:05:45.593
to fight together...

23
00:05:47.259 --> 00:05:49.759
and die together

24
00:05:49.843 --> 00:05:51.800
so that others might live.

25
00:05:54.384 --> 00:05:56.718
Everyone in this world

26
00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:59.593
owes them a debt
that can never be repaid.

27
00:06:01.050 --> 00:06:03.966
It is our duty and our honor

28
00:06:04.050 --> 00:06:07.259
to keep them alive in memory...

29
00:06:08.425 --> 00:06:10.134
for those who come after us...

30
00:06:11.343 --> 00:06:13.259
and those
who come after them...

31
00:06:15.134 --> 00:06:18.134
for as long as men draw breath.

32
00:06:20.050 --> 00:06:23.550
They were the shields
that guarded the realms of men.

33
00:06:24.925 --> 00:06:27.759
And we shall never see
their like again.

34
00:08:59.259 --> 00:09:00.884
To your health.

35
00:09:27.884 --> 00:09:29.342
Have you seen Arya?

36
00:09:30.884 --> 00:09:32.717
You can still smell
the burning bodies.

37
00:09:32.801 --> 00:09:34.301
and that's
where your head is at.

38
00:09:34.384 --> 00:09:37.384
- I just want to thank her for...
- I'm sure you do.

39
00:09:37.467 --> 00:09:38.717
Look. it's not about that.

40
00:09:38.801 --> 00:09:40.551
Of course it's about that.
you twat.

41
00:09:40.634 --> 00:09:41.717
Why shouldn't it be?

42
00:09:41.801 --> 00:09:45.009
The dead are dead. You're not.

43
00:09:58.342 --> 00:09:59.842
Gendry.

44
00:10:02.259 --> 00:10:03.676
That's right. isn't it?

45
00:10:10.176 --> 00:10:11.259
Yes. Your Grace.

46
00:10:11.342 --> 00:10:13.551
You're Robert Baratheon's son.

47
00:10:19.926 --> 00:10:21.884
You are aware
he took my family's throne

48
00:10:21.966 --> 00:10:24.301
and tried to have me murdered?

49
00:10:24.384 --> 00:10:27.926
I didn't even know he was my
father until after he was dead.

50
00:10:28.009 --> 00:10:31.216
Yes. he's dead.

51
00:10:31.301 --> 00:10:32.884
His brothers are too.

52
00:10:34.342 --> 00:10:37.009
So who's Lord
of Storm's End now?

53
00:10:38.759 --> 00:10:40.009
I don't know. Your Grace.

54
00:10:40.091 --> 00:10:41.926
Does anyone?

55
00:10:52.216 --> 00:10:54.592
I think you should be
Lord of Storm's End.

56
00:11:00.301 --> 00:11:01.551
I can't be. I'm a bastard.

57
00:11:01.634 --> 00:11:06.134
No. you are Lord
Gendry Baratheon of Storm's End.

58
00:11:06.216 --> 00:11:09.384
the lawful son
of Robert Baratheon.

59
00:11:09.467 --> 00:11:12.216
Because that
is what I have made you.

60
00:11:21.259 --> 00:11:25.176
To Lord Gendry Baratheon
of Storm's End.

61
00:11:25.259 --> 00:11:27.467
To Gendry!

62
00:11:27.551 --> 00:11:29.759
Lord Gendry!

63
00:11:29.842 --> 00:11:31.759
Gendry!

64
00:11:31.842 --> 00:11:34.259
- Gendry!
- Gendry!

65
00:11:36.176 --> 00:11:37.926
Lord Gendry!

66
00:11:39.259 --> 00:11:40.259
Gendry!

67
00:11:43.426 --> 00:11:45.216
That's easy. isn't it?

68
00:11:47.551 --> 00:11:50.676
- A fitting reward for a hero.
- Uh. hold on.

69
00:11:50.759 --> 00:11:54.551
And a Lord of Storm's End
who will be forever loyal to you.

70
00:11:54.634 --> 00:11:56.467
- Come. my lord.
- See?

71
00:11:56.551 --> 00:11:58.926
You're not the only one
who's clever.

72
00:12:08.634 --> 00:12:11.592
I have to go down and get another barrel.

73
00:12:14.926 --> 00:12:17.801
We fought dead things
and lived to talk about it.

74
00:12:17.884 --> 00:12:21.091
If this isn't the time to drink.
when is?

75
00:12:31.384 --> 00:12:32.926
The last time I saw her.

76
00:12:33.009 --> 00:12:36.301
I told her I'd kill her
if I ever saw her again.

77
00:12:36.384 --> 00:12:39.134
- I'm sure you had your reasons.
- I did.

78
00:12:39.216 --> 00:12:41.676
- I do.
- So did you?

79
00:12:43.842 --> 00:12:45.759
Never got the chance.

80
00:12:45.842 --> 00:12:47.342
She did it to herself.

81
00:12:49.592 --> 00:12:51.509
Or her god did it to her.

82
00:12:54.051 --> 00:12:55.717
Lord of Light.

83
00:12:55.801 --> 00:13:00.091
We play his game for him.
we fight his war and win.

84
00:13:00.176 --> 00:13:01.801
and then

85
00:13:01.884 --> 00:13:03.176
he fucks off.

86
00:13:03.259 --> 00:13:06.634
No signs. no blessings.
Who knows what he wants?

87
00:13:08.134 --> 00:13:10.216
I don't imagine
thinking about that subject

88
00:13:10.301 --> 00:13:12.091
will leave you
any happier than before.

89
00:13:12.176 --> 00:13:14.342
And what if
I'm not trying to be happy?

90
00:13:16.676 --> 00:13:17.801
Then you're in luck.

91
00:13:20.301 --> 00:13:22.717
We may have defeated them.

92
00:13:22.801 --> 00:13:25.717
but we still have us
to contend with.

93
00:13:30.676 --> 00:13:32.759
Thank you. I feel much better.

94
00:13:46.384 --> 00:13:47.426
More ale!

95
00:13:50.009 --> 00:13:51.342
This is clever.

96
00:13:52.759 --> 00:13:55.216
Even better than the saddle
I designed for you.

97
00:13:56.551 --> 00:13:58.842
It's the same as the one
Daeron Targaryen built

98
00:13:58.926 --> 00:14:02.592
for his crippled nephew
120 years ago.

99
00:14:02.676 --> 00:14:04.509
I liked that one.

100
00:14:04.592 --> 00:14:07.759
You know our history
better than anyone.

101
00:14:07.842 --> 00:14:10.966
That will be useful
as Lord of Winterfell.

102
00:14:11.051 --> 00:14:13.009
I'm not Lord of Winterfell.

103
00:14:13.091 --> 00:14:16.091
You're the only surviving
trueborn son of Ned Stark.

104
00:14:20.966 --> 00:14:22.551
You don't want it.

105
00:14:22.634 --> 00:14:25.051
I don't really want anymore.

106
00:14:27.091 --> 00:14:28.426
I envy you.

107
00:14:31.426 --> 00:14:33.259
You shouldn't envy me.

108
00:14:34.759 --> 00:14:36.759
Mostly I live in the past.

109
00:14:42.134 --> 00:14:43.551
- All of it.
- Go on.

110
00:14:43.634 --> 00:14:46.216
- No. not in one go.
- Go on. I believe in you.

111
00:14:46.301 --> 00:14:48.342
We have to celebrate our victory.

112
00:14:48.426 --> 00:14:50.717
Vomiting is not celebrating.

113
00:14:50.801 --> 00:14:52.592
Yes. it is.

114
00:14:52.676 --> 00:14:53.966
Ah!

115
00:14:54.051 --> 00:14:55.551
To the Dragon Queen!

116
00:14:57.966 --> 00:15:01.091
To Arya Stark.
the hero of Winterfell!

117
00:15:04.676 --> 00:15:06.884
- Rah! Rah! Rah! Rah!
- Drink!

118
00:15:19.634 --> 00:15:21.467
I'm fine!

119
00:15:34.842 --> 00:15:35.842
Your turn.

120
00:15:35.926 --> 00:15:37.509
Um...

121
00:15:38.384 --> 00:15:41.509
You are an only child.

122
00:15:42.634 --> 00:15:44.259
- I told you I was.
- You didn't.

123
00:15:44.342 --> 00:15:47.176
- I did.
- I surmised it.

124
00:15:47.259 --> 00:15:48.801
Drink.

125
00:15:49.801 --> 00:15:51.051
Go again.

126
00:15:51.134 --> 00:15:52.467
Why does he get to go again?

127
00:15:52.551 --> 00:15:54.426
Because it's my game.

128
00:15:54.509 --> 00:15:58.134
You have danced
with Renly Baratheon.

129
00:16:00.176 --> 00:16:01.009
No.

130
00:16:01.091 --> 00:16:02.467
Drink.

131
00:16:03.592 --> 00:16:05.384
The other way around!

132
00:16:05.467 --> 00:16:07.676
I saw him riding that thing.

133
00:16:07.759 --> 00:16:10.509
- We all did.
- No. No.

134
00:16:10.592 --> 00:16:13.842
I saw him riding that thing.

135
00:16:13.926 --> 00:16:15.926
- That's right. you did.
- I did.

136
00:16:16.009 --> 00:16:19.759
That's why we all agreed
to follow him.

137
00:16:19.842 --> 00:16:22.051
That's the kind of man he is.

138
00:16:23.801 --> 00:16:25.216
He's little...

139
00:16:26.216 --> 00:16:27.801
...but he's strong.

140
00:16:27.884 --> 00:16:30.759
Strong enough
to befriend an enemy

141
00:16:30.842 --> 00:16:32.091
and get murdered for it!

142
00:16:33.176 --> 00:16:35.467
Most people get bloody murdered.

143
00:16:35.551 --> 00:16:36.759
they stay that way.

144
00:16:36.842 --> 00:16:38.467
Not this one.

145
00:16:40.051 --> 00:16:42.259
Yeah.
I didn't have much say in that.

146
00:16:42.342 --> 00:16:45.384
Ah! He comes back
and keeps fighting.

147
00:16:45.467 --> 00:16:48.966
Here. north of the Wall.
and then back here again.

148
00:16:49.051 --> 00:16:52.509
He keeps fighting.
He keeps fighting.

149
00:16:52.592 --> 00:16:55.509
He climbed on a fucking dragon
and fought.

150
00:16:55.592 --> 00:16:58.176
What kind of person
climbs on a fucking dragon?

151
00:16:58.259 --> 00:17:01.509
A madman or a king!

152
00:17:16.092 --> 00:17:18.843
- Drink.
- Drink.

153
00:17:18.925 --> 00:17:19.925
Drink.

154
00:17:50.593 --> 00:17:51.675
Wrong!

155
00:17:51.759 --> 00:17:53.843
Wrong. wrong. wrong! Drink!

156
00:17:55.967 --> 00:17:57.134
Mm!

157
00:17:57.217 --> 00:18:00.468
You were married. Before Sansa.

158
00:18:01.343 --> 00:18:02.634
Drink.

159
00:18:07.759 --> 00:18:09.884
You're drinking wine.
but you prefer ale!

160
00:18:09.967 --> 00:18:10.967
No!

161
00:18:24.800 --> 00:18:25.843
You're a virgin.

162
00:18:31.384 --> 00:18:33.092
That's a statement
about the present.

163
00:18:33.175 --> 00:18:36.092
At no point in the past.
up until this very moment.

164
00:18:36.175 --> 00:18:38.175
have you slept with a man.

165
00:18:39.800 --> 00:18:40.843
Or a woman.

166
00:18:47.217 --> 00:18:49.009
I have to piss.

167
00:18:49.092 --> 00:18:53.092
We did it!
We faced those icy fucks.

168
00:18:53.175 --> 00:18:55.759
Looked right
into their blue eyes.

169
00:18:55.843 --> 00:18:57.217
and here we are.

170
00:18:58.675 --> 00:19:02.134
Now. which one of you cowards
shit in my pants?

171
00:19:05.800 --> 00:19:07.967
Please pardon me for a moment.

172
00:19:27.593 --> 00:19:29.009
Drink it!

173
00:19:50.425 --> 00:19:52.593
And after all that.

174
00:19:52.675 --> 00:19:56.217
this fucker comes north
and takes her from me.

175
00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:58.217
Just takes her. like that.

176
00:20:00.217 --> 00:20:01.843
I mean it. Clegane.

177
00:20:01.925 --> 00:20:03.509
My heart is broken.

178
00:20:03.593 --> 00:20:04.843
Don't touch me.

179
00:20:04.925 --> 00:20:06.259
You can touch me.

180
00:20:07.550 --> 00:20:09.593
I'm not afraid of wildlings.

181
00:20:09.675 --> 00:20:11.425
Maybe you should be.

182
00:20:15.759 --> 00:20:17.050
Well. Clegane...

183
00:20:18.175 --> 00:20:20.675
it's time to drown our sorrows.

184
00:20:20.759 --> 00:20:22.425
I'm not done with my drink.

185
00:20:23.550 --> 00:20:25.425
You saved the day.

186
00:20:25.509 --> 00:20:26.884
You owe me one.

187
00:20:26.967 --> 00:20:30.468
- Don't forget that.
- For the rest of my days.

188
00:20:31.884 --> 00:20:33.050
Are you ready now?

189
00:20:33.134 --> 00:20:35.259
This is my drink.

190
00:20:40.800 --> 00:20:42.509
All right!

191
00:20:50.259 --> 00:20:53.300
She could have made you happy.
for a little while.

192
00:20:56.259 --> 00:20:58.800
There's only one thing
that'll make me happy.

193
00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:00.718
And what's that?

194
00:21:00.800 --> 00:21:03.175
That's my fucking business.

195
00:21:07.884 --> 00:21:10.718
Used to be
you couldn't look at me.

196
00:21:10.800 --> 00:21:13.050
That was a long time ago.

197
00:21:13.134 --> 00:21:15.843
I've seen much worse than you
since then.

198
00:21:15.925 --> 00:21:17.884
Yes. I've heard.

199
00:21:17.967 --> 00:21:19.718
Heard you were broken in.

200
00:21:20.718 --> 00:21:22.343
Heard you were broken in rough.

201
00:21:23.468 --> 00:21:25.800
And he got what he deserved.

202
00:21:25.884 --> 00:21:27.217
I gave it to him.

203
00:21:28.593 --> 00:21:29.634
How?

204
00:21:30.925 --> 00:21:32.050
Hounds.

205
00:21:35.884 --> 00:21:37.550
You've changed. Little Bird.

206
00:21:44.009 --> 00:21:45.384
None of it would have happened

207
00:21:45.468 --> 00:21:47.300
if you'd left King's Landing
with me.

208
00:21:47.384 --> 00:21:50.384
No Littlefinger. no Ramsay...

209
00:21:52.009 --> 00:21:53.259
none of it.

210
00:22:01.634 --> 00:22:04.175
Without Littlefinger.
and Ramsay and the rest.

211
00:22:04.259 --> 00:22:06.759
I would have stayed
a Little Bird all my life.

212
00:22:28.259 --> 00:22:31.384
- Hey!
- Pour another one.

213
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:44.967
Don't shoot.

214
00:22:48.009 --> 00:22:50.884
It's nighttime. it's freezing.
and everyone's celebrating.

215
00:22:50.967 --> 00:22:53.468
You should be celebrating
with them.

216
00:22:53.550 --> 00:22:54.925
I am celebrating.

217
00:22:56.800 --> 00:22:58.759
Yeah. I am too.

218
00:23:01.009 --> 00:23:02.925
I'm not Gendry Rivers anymore.

219
00:23:03.009 --> 00:23:06.384
I'm Gendry Baratheon.
Lord of Storm's End.

220
00:23:06.468 --> 00:23:08.800
By order of the queen.

221
00:23:10.509 --> 00:23:11.800
Congratulations.

222
00:23:15.092 --> 00:23:17.050
I don't know how to be
lord of anything.

223
00:23:17.134 --> 00:23:18.759
I hardly know
how to use a fork.

224
00:23:18.843 --> 00:23:20.759
All I know
is that you're beautiful.

225
00:23:20.843 --> 00:23:21.967
and I love you.

226
00:23:22.050 --> 00:23:23.884
and none of it
will be worth anything

227
00:23:23.967 --> 00:23:25.134
if you're not with me.

228
00:23:26.468 --> 00:23:27.468
So be with me.

229
00:23:31.967 --> 00:23:35.593
Be my wife.
Be the Lady of Storm's End.

230
00:23:57.675 --> 00:24:00.092
You'll be a wonderful lord.

231
00:24:00.175 --> 00:24:03.217
and any lady
would be lucky to have you.

232
00:24:04.593 --> 00:24:06.050
But I'm not a lady.

233
00:24:07.468 --> 00:24:08.843
I never have been.

234
00:24:11.175 --> 00:24:12.175
That's not me.

235
00:24:38.343 --> 00:24:39.718
You didn't drink.

236
00:24:42.550 --> 00:24:45.593
- I didn't drink?
- In the game.

237
00:24:45.675 --> 00:24:48.843
- I drank.
- In the game. This is Dornish.

238
00:24:51.718 --> 00:24:55.259
This is not the game.
This is only drinking.

239
00:24:56.300 --> 00:24:57.425
Suit yourself.

240
00:25:08.384 --> 00:25:10.759
You keep it
warm enough in here.

241
00:25:14.134 --> 00:25:17.134
It's the first thing I learnt
when I came to the North.

242
00:25:17.217 --> 00:25:18.593
Keep your fire going.

243
00:25:18.675 --> 00:25:21.009
Every time you leave the room.
put more wood on.

244
00:25:21.092 --> 00:25:23.718
That's very diligent.
Very responsible.

245
00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:25.675
- Piss off.
- You know the first thing

246
00:25:25.759 --> 00:25:27.550
I learned in the North?

247
00:25:27.634 --> 00:25:29.718
I hate the fucking North.

248
00:25:30.884 --> 00:25:32.092
It grows on you.

249
00:25:33.800 --> 00:25:36.425
I don't want things
growing on me.

250
00:25:37.675 --> 00:25:41.009
How about Tormund Giantsbane?

251
00:25:41.092 --> 00:25:42.593
Has he grown on you?

252
00:25:44.259 --> 00:25:46.259
He was very sad when you left.

253
00:25:47.759 --> 00:25:49.593
You sound quite jealous.

254
00:25:52.425 --> 00:25:53.925
I do. don't I?

255
00:25:58.967 --> 00:26:00.800
It's bloody hot in here.

256
00:26:10.593 --> 00:26:11.967
Oh. move aside.

257
00:26:17.634 --> 00:26:18.675
What are you doing?

258
00:26:19.675 --> 00:26:21.134
I'm taking your shirt off.

259
00:27:08.009 --> 00:27:10.343
I've never slept with
a knight before.

260
00:27:11.593 --> 00:27:14.300
I've never slept
with anyone before.

261
00:27:16.217 --> 00:27:18.925
Then you have to drink.
Those are the rules.

262
00:27:20.009 --> 00:27:21.384
I told you...

263
00:27:36.884 --> 00:27:38.384
Are you drunk?

264
00:27:43.050 --> 00:27:44.050
No.

265
00:27:49.050 --> 00:27:50.343
Only a little.

266
00:28:00.509 --> 00:28:02.217
I didn't know Ser Jorah well...

267
00:28:03.634 --> 00:28:04.884
but I know this.

268
00:28:06.593 --> 00:28:08.509
If he could have chosen
a way to die.

269
00:28:08.593 --> 00:28:10.593
it would have been
protecting you.

270
00:28:11.634 --> 00:28:12.634
He loved me.

271
00:28:15.593 --> 00:28:17.718
And I couldn't love him back.

272
00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:21.550
Not the way he wanted.

273
00:28:25.009 --> 00:28:26.634
Not the way I love you.

274
00:28:29.759 --> 00:28:31.217
Is that all right?

275
00:29:10.509 --> 00:29:12.593
I wish you'd never told me.

276
00:29:13.843 --> 00:29:16.634
If I didn't know.
I'd be happy right now.

277
00:29:18.092 --> 00:29:19.300
I try to forget.

278
00:29:20.967 --> 00:29:22.343
Tonight I did for a while.

279
00:29:22.425 --> 00:29:25.217
and then I saw them
gathered around you.

280
00:29:26.509 --> 00:29:29.050
I saw the way
they looked at you.

281
00:29:30.134 --> 00:29:31.509
I know that look.

282
00:29:33.175 --> 00:29:36.675
So many people have looked at me
that way. but never here.

283
00:29:36.759 --> 00:29:38.343
Never on this side of the sea.

284
00:29:39.800 --> 00:29:41.092
I told you I don't want it.

285
00:29:41.175 --> 00:29:43.718
It doesn't matter what you want.

286
00:29:43.800 --> 00:29:45.593
You didn't want to be
King in the North.

287
00:29:45.675 --> 00:29:48.259
What happens when they demand
you press your claim.

288
00:29:48.343 --> 00:29:49.843
and take what is mine?

289
00:29:53.300 --> 00:29:55.134
I'll refuse.

290
00:29:55.217 --> 00:29:57.759
You are my queen. I don't know
what else I can say.

291
00:29:57.843 --> 00:30:00.050
You can say nothing.

292
00:30:00.134 --> 00:30:01.593
To anyone. ever.

293
00:30:01.675 --> 00:30:03.675
Never tell them
who you really are.

294
00:30:03.759 --> 00:30:06.175
Swear your brother
and Samwell Tarly to secrecy.

295
00:30:06.259 --> 00:30:07.468
and tell no one else.

296
00:30:07.550 --> 00:30:09.175
Or it will take on
a life of its own

297
00:30:09.259 --> 00:30:10.967
and you won't be able
to control it

298
00:30:11.050 --> 00:30:12.259
or what it does to people.

299
00:30:12.343 --> 00:30:14.843
No matter how many times
you bend the knee.

300
00:30:14.925 --> 00:30:16.884
no matter what you swear.

301
00:30:22.050 --> 00:30:25.509
I want it to be the way it was
between us.

302
00:30:34.718 --> 00:30:36.509
I have to tell Sansa and Arya.

303
00:30:36.593 --> 00:30:42.967
Sansa will want to see me gone
and you on the Iron Throne.

304
00:30:43.050 --> 00:30:44.718
She won't.

305
00:30:44.800 --> 00:30:47.843
She's not the girl
you grew up with.

306
00:30:47.925 --> 00:30:50.217
Not after what she's seen.

307
00:30:50.300 --> 00:30:52.925
not after
what they've done to her.

308
00:30:56.300 --> 00:30:58.175
I owe them the truth.

309
00:30:58.259 --> 00:31:01.134
Even if the truth destroys us?

310
00:31:01.217 --> 00:31:02.925
- It won't.
- It will.

311
00:31:05.468 --> 00:31:07.259
I've never begged
for anything...

312
00:31:08.509 --> 00:31:10.675
but I'm begging you.

313
00:31:10.759 --> 00:31:13.759
Don't do this. Please.

314
00:31:20.384 --> 00:31:21.759
You are my queen.

315
00:31:23.343 --> 00:31:25.217
Nothing will change that.

316
00:31:28.134 --> 00:31:29.843
And they are my family.

317
00:31:31.800 --> 00:31:33.468
We can live together.

318
00:31:39.384 --> 00:31:40.384
We can.

319
00:31:42.550 --> 00:31:44.300
I've just told you how.

320
00:32:20.425 --> 00:32:22.300
Half are gone.

321
00:32:26.134 --> 00:32:27.634
The Northmen as well.

322
00:32:34.009 --> 00:32:37.175
And the Golden Company
has arrived in King's Landing.

323
00:32:37.259 --> 00:32:39.259
courtesy of the Greyjoy fleet.

324
00:32:39.343 --> 00:32:43.050
The balance has grown
distressingly even.

325
00:32:43.134 --> 00:32:45.925
When the people find out
what we have done for them.

326
00:32:46.009 --> 00:32:47.259
that we saved them...

327
00:32:47.343 --> 00:32:49.675
Cersei will make sure
they don't believe it.

328
00:32:51.675 --> 00:32:53.300
We will hit her hard.

329
00:32:53.384 --> 00:32:55.593
We will rip her out
root and stem.

330
00:32:57.050 --> 00:32:59.675
The objective here
is to remove Cersei

331
00:32:59.759 --> 00:33:02.425
without destroying
King's Landing.

332
00:33:05.550 --> 00:33:09.384
Thankfully.
she's losing allies by the day.

333
00:33:09.468 --> 00:33:12.300
Yara Greyjoy has retaken
the Iron Islands

334
00:33:12.384 --> 00:33:13.675
in her queen's name.

335
00:33:13.759 --> 00:33:16.425
The new Prince of Dorne
pledges his support.

336
00:33:16.509 --> 00:33:18.550
No matter how many lords
turn against her.

337
00:33:18.634 --> 00:33:20.425
as long as she sits
on the Iron Throne.

338
00:33:20.509 --> 00:33:23.217
she can call herself
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

339
00:33:25.550 --> 00:33:27.300
We need the capital.

340
00:33:27.384 --> 00:33:29.134
I watched the people
of King's Landing

341
00:33:29.217 --> 00:33:31.509
rebel against their king
when they were hungry.

342
00:33:31.593 --> 00:33:33.800
and that was before
winter began.

343
00:33:33.884 --> 00:33:37.425
Give them the opportunity
and they will cast Cersei aside.

344
00:33:39.134 --> 00:33:41.509
We'll surround the city.

345
00:33:41.593 --> 00:33:43.843
If the Iron Fleet
tries to ferry in more food.

346
00:33:43.925 --> 00:33:46.009
the dragons will destroy them.

347
00:33:46.092 --> 00:33:48.509
If the Lannisters
and the Golden Company attack.

348
00:33:48.593 --> 00:33:50.259
we'll defeat them in the field.

349
00:33:50.343 --> 00:33:54.009
Once the people see
that Cersei is our only enemy.

350
00:33:54.092 --> 00:33:56.092
her reign is over.

351
00:34:01.259 --> 00:34:02.718
All right.

352
00:34:02.800 --> 00:34:05.925
The men we have left are exhausted.

353
00:34:06.009 --> 00:34:07.217
Many of them are wounded.

354
00:34:07.300 --> 00:34:09.175
They'll fight better
if they have time

355
00:34:09.259 --> 00:34:10.635
to rest and recuperate.

356
00:34:11.925 --> 00:34:13.134
How long do you suggest?

357
00:34:14.300 --> 00:34:15.800
I can't say for certain.

358
00:34:15.885 --> 00:34:17.925
not without
talking to the officers.

359
00:34:21.300 --> 00:34:24.175
I came north
to fight alongside you

360
00:34:24.259 --> 00:34:26.800
at great cost
to my armies and myself.

361
00:34:28.050 --> 00:34:30.885
Now that the time has come
to reciprocate.

362
00:34:30.967 --> 00:34:32.760
you want to postpone.

363
00:34:32.842 --> 00:34:35.717
It's not just our people.
It's yours.

364
00:34:35.800 --> 00:34:37.425
You want to throw them
into a war

365
00:34:37.509 --> 00:34:39.050
they're not ready to fight?

366
00:34:39.134 --> 00:34:40.842
The longer I leave
my enemies alone.

367
00:34:40.925 --> 00:34:42.425
the stronger they become.

368
00:34:45.967 --> 00:34:49.509
The Northern forces
will honor their promises

369
00:34:49.592 --> 00:34:50.885
and their allegiance

370
00:34:50.967 --> 00:34:53.467
to the Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms.

371
00:34:58.842 --> 00:35:00.675
What you command. we will obey.

372
00:35:05.425 --> 00:35:07.009
So...

373
00:35:07.092 --> 00:35:10.009
if all are in agreement...

374
00:35:10.092 --> 00:35:12.925
Jon and Ser Davos
will ride down the Kingsroad

375
00:35:13.009 --> 00:35:14.384
with the Northern troops

376
00:35:14.467 --> 00:35:17.009
and the bulk of the remaining
Dothraki and Unsullied.

377
00:35:17.092 --> 00:35:19.425
A smaller group of us
will ride to White Harbor.

378
00:35:19.509 --> 00:35:21.425
and sail from there
to Dragonstone

379
00:35:21.509 --> 00:35:25.217
with our queen and her dragons
accompanying us from above.

380
00:35:25.300 --> 00:35:27.967
Ser Jaime has chosen
to remain here.

381
00:35:28.050 --> 00:35:30.342
as a guest
of the Lady of Winterfell.

382
00:35:33.384 --> 00:35:35.300
We have won the Great War.

383
00:35:36.300 --> 00:35:38.050
Now we will win the Last War.

384
00:35:39.342 --> 00:35:41.342
In all Seven Kingdoms.

385
00:35:41.425 --> 00:35:44.217
men will live
without fear and cruelty

386
00:35:45.300 --> 00:35:46.717
under their rightful queen.

387
00:36:00.175 --> 00:36:01.342
We need a word.

388
00:36:05.467 --> 00:36:08.425
You understand we'd all be dead
if not for her.

389
00:36:08.509 --> 00:36:10.800
We'd be corpses
marching down to King's Landing.

390
00:36:10.885 --> 00:36:12.360
Arya's the one
that killed the Night King.

391
00:36:12.384 --> 00:36:14.467
Her men gave their lives
defending Winterfell...

392
00:36:14.550 --> 00:36:16.134
And we will never forget them.

393
00:36:16.217 --> 00:36:18.152
That doesn't mean that I want
to kneel to someone who...

394
00:36:18.175 --> 00:36:20.842
I swore myself and the North
to her cause.

395
00:36:20.925 --> 00:36:22.467
I respect that.

396
00:36:25.092 --> 00:36:26.760
You respect it?

397
00:36:27.467 --> 00:36:29.217
We needed her.

398
00:36:30.592 --> 00:36:33.217
We needed her army. her dragons.

399
00:36:35.009 --> 00:36:36.800
You did the right thing.

400
00:36:36.885 --> 00:36:39.300
And we're doing the right thing
telling you

401
00:36:39.384 --> 00:36:40.925
we don't trust your queen.

402
00:36:42.842 --> 00:36:45.134
- You don't know her yet.
- I'll never know her.

403
00:36:45.217 --> 00:36:46.509
She's not one of us.

404
00:36:46.592 --> 00:36:48.509
If you only trust the people
you grew up with.

405
00:36:48.592 --> 00:36:49.925
you won't make many allies.

406
00:36:50.009 --> 00:36:51.550
That's all right.

407
00:36:51.635 --> 00:36:53.760
I don't need many allies.

408
00:36:53.842 --> 00:36:56.092
- Arya...
- We're family.

409
00:36:57.425 --> 00:36:58.635
The four of us.

410
00:36:59.717 --> 00:37:01.425
The last of the Starks.

411
00:37:05.467 --> 00:37:06.925
I've never been a Stark.

412
00:37:08.092 --> 00:37:09.675
You are.

413
00:37:09.760 --> 00:37:12.760
You're just as much
Ned Stark's child as any of us.

414
00:37:12.842 --> 00:37:14.717
You're my brother.

415
00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:17.300
Not my half-brother
or my bastard brother.

416
00:37:18.134 --> 00:37:19.675
My brother.

417
00:37:27.217 --> 00:37:28.967
It's your choice.

418
00:37:36.134 --> 00:37:38.342
I need to tell you something.

419
00:37:39.842 --> 00:37:43.342
But you have to swear
you'll never tell another soul.

420
00:37:46.635 --> 00:37:47.967
What is it?

421
00:37:49.259 --> 00:37:52.300
You have to swear it.
before I tell you.

422
00:37:52.384 --> 00:37:53.967
How can I promise
to keep a secret

423
00:37:54.050 --> 00:37:55.592
if I don't even
know what it is?

424
00:37:55.675 --> 00:37:57.342
Because we're family.

425
00:38:02.425 --> 00:38:03.425
Swear it.

426
00:38:04.717 --> 00:38:06.134
I swear it.

427
00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:11.800
I swear it.

428
00:38:19.842 --> 00:38:21.134
Tell them.

429
00:38:31.675 --> 00:38:34.217
So she's going to stay here with you?

430
00:38:36.675 --> 00:38:39.885
She's sworn to protect
the Stark girls. so...

431
00:38:43.217 --> 00:38:44.675
Say something snide.

432
00:38:45.885 --> 00:38:46.885
I'm happy.

433
00:38:46.967 --> 00:38:48.717
I'm happy that you're happy.

434
00:38:51.635 --> 00:38:55.009
I'm happy that you'll finally
have to climb for it.

435
00:38:57.050 --> 00:39:00.342
Do you know how long I've waited
to tell tall-person jokes?

436
00:39:01.550 --> 00:39:03.842
To climbing mountains.

437
00:39:03.925 --> 00:39:05.384
To climbing mountains.

438
00:39:07.967 --> 00:39:10.967
- What's she like down there?
- What?

439
00:39:11.050 --> 00:39:13.009
That's not your concern.

440
00:39:13.092 --> 00:39:15.635
I haven't been with a woman
for years.

441
00:39:15.717 --> 00:39:17.217
- Give me a morsel.
- You're a dog.

442
00:39:17.300 --> 00:39:19.175
I am the Imp.
and I demand to know.

443
00:39:19.259 --> 00:39:21.050
I knew you were fucking her.

444
00:39:22.967 --> 00:39:24.885
A pair of tall. blond toffs.

445
00:39:24.967 --> 00:39:26.635
Must be like
looking in the mirror.

446
00:39:26.717 --> 00:39:28.550
Ser Bronn of the Blackwater.

447
00:39:30.175 --> 00:39:31.925
Where's your drink?

448
00:39:32.009 --> 00:39:34.134
What are you...
What are you doing up North?

449
00:39:34.217 --> 00:39:35.675
What are you doing with that?

450
00:39:35.760 --> 00:39:37.300
Oh. this?

451
00:39:37.384 --> 00:39:38.425
This is for you.

452
00:39:39.925 --> 00:39:41.009
For both of you.

453
00:39:41.092 --> 00:39:43.175
You're supposed to be south.

454
00:39:43.259 --> 00:39:45.175
You boys are a pair
of gold-plated cunts.

455
00:39:45.259 --> 00:39:46.818
- Do you know that?
- That's a bit rude.

456
00:39:46.842 --> 00:39:49.050
Year after year.
I've shoveled Lannister shit.

457
00:39:49.134 --> 00:39:52.050
- and what do I have to show?
- You're a knight. thanks to me.

458
00:39:52.134 --> 00:39:53.777
Thanks to me.
And that title's worth as much

459
00:39:53.800 --> 00:39:56.009
as a blond hair
from your brother's ballsack.

460
00:39:56.092 --> 00:39:57.675
Power resides
where men believe...

461
00:39:57.760 --> 00:39:59.717
Shut your mouth.

462
00:39:59.800 --> 00:40:02.134
- I'm just trying...
- I've never hit a dwarf before.

463
00:40:02.217 --> 00:40:04.092
but say another word
and I will belt you.

464
00:40:04.175 --> 00:40:06.717
See. I don't believe
you'd do that. after all...

465
00:40:06.800 --> 00:40:08.550
You couldn't do it
on your best day.

466
00:40:08.635 --> 00:40:09.717
you one-handed fuck.

467
00:40:09.800 --> 00:40:11.384
And your best days
are long gone.

468
00:40:11.467 --> 00:40:12.967
You broke my nose!

469
00:40:13.050 --> 00:40:14.818
- I did not break your nose.
- How do you know?

470
00:40:14.842 --> 00:40:17.134
Because I've been breaking noses
since I was your size.

471
00:40:17.217 --> 00:40:20.134
and I know what it sounds like.
Now listen.

472
00:40:20.217 --> 00:40:22.800
Your sister
offered me Riverrun.

473
00:40:22.885 --> 00:40:24.384
Nice big castle. good lands.

474
00:40:24.467 --> 00:40:26.509
plenty of peasants
who do what they're told.

475
00:40:26.592 --> 00:40:29.259
- And you trust Cersei...
- I knew your sister was dead

476
00:40:29.342 --> 00:40:31.134
the second I saw those dragons.

477
00:40:31.217 --> 00:40:32.800
Now.
your army may be torn to shit.

478
00:40:32.885 --> 00:40:35.092
but I'd still bet
on your Dragon Queen to win.

479
00:40:35.175 --> 00:40:37.675
And it just so happens
I'm a betting man.

480
00:40:38.925 --> 00:40:41.842
If Cersei's dead.
she can't pay up.

481
00:40:44.175 --> 00:40:46.342
Mmm. that's good.
Of course. the odds change

482
00:40:46.425 --> 00:40:48.425
if the Dragon Queen's Hand
turns up dead.

483
00:40:48.509 --> 00:40:51.384
Maybe a few of her top generals
get picked off one by one.

484
00:40:51.467 --> 00:40:53.384
- All of a sudden...
- May I speak?

485
00:40:53.467 --> 00:40:56.134
Why not?
Only death will shut you up.

486
00:40:59.509 --> 00:41:02.342
We made a deal long ago.
Do you remember?

487
00:41:02.425 --> 00:41:03.592
If anyone offered me money

488
00:41:03.675 --> 00:41:05.925
to kill you.
you'd pay me double.

489
00:41:06.009 --> 00:41:07.467
What's double Riverrun?

490
00:41:08.509 --> 00:41:09.509
Highgarden.

491
00:41:11.675 --> 00:41:13.175
You could be Lord of the Reach.

492
00:41:13.259 --> 00:41:16.092
- Highgarden? Are you mad?
- It's better than being dead.

493
00:41:16.175 --> 00:41:17.384
He's not going to kill us.

494
00:41:17.467 --> 00:41:19.217
He wouldn't be
talking to us if...

495
00:41:22.217 --> 00:41:23.467
The way I see it.

496
00:41:23.550 --> 00:41:26.217
I only need one
of the Lannister brothers alive.

497
00:41:26.300 --> 00:41:28.425
Highgarden will never belong
to a cutthroat.

498
00:41:28.509 --> 00:41:30.635
No? Who were your ancestors.

499
00:41:30.717 --> 00:41:32.885
the ones
who made your family rich?

500
00:41:32.967 --> 00:41:34.550
Fancy lads in silk?

501
00:41:34.635 --> 00:41:36.300
They were fucking cutthroats.

502
00:41:36.384 --> 00:41:38.800
That's how all the great houses
started. isn't it?

503
00:41:38.885 --> 00:41:41.300
With a hard bastard
who was good at killing people.

504
00:41:41.384 --> 00:41:43.717
Kill a few hundred people.
they make you a lord.

505
00:41:43.800 --> 00:41:45.800
Kill a few thousand.
they make you king.

506
00:41:45.885 --> 00:41:50.300
And then all your cocksucking
grandsons can ruin the family

507
00:41:50.384 --> 00:41:51.925
with their cocksucking ways.

508
00:41:55.760 --> 00:41:56.760
Highgarden.

509
00:41:58.550 --> 00:42:00.092
Give me your word.

510
00:42:01.842 --> 00:42:03.300
You have my word.

511
00:42:05.175 --> 00:42:08.550
None of this means a thing
until we take King's Landing.

512
00:42:09.675 --> 00:42:12.092
We ride south in the morning.

513
00:42:12.175 --> 00:42:13.342
We could use an officer

514
00:42:13.425 --> 00:42:15.675
with knowledge
of the city's defenses.

515
00:42:15.760 --> 00:42:17.009
Oh. no.

516
00:42:17.092 --> 00:42:19.675
No. my fighting days are done.

517
00:42:19.760 --> 00:42:22.800
But I still got a few
killing days left. you hear me?

518
00:42:22.885 --> 00:42:25.509
I'll come find you
when the war is done.

519
00:42:25.592 --> 00:42:27.885
Till then. don't die.

520
00:42:52.675 --> 00:42:54.800
For fuck's sake.

521
00:42:56.342 --> 00:42:57.425
On your own?

522
00:42:58.635 --> 00:43:00.134
Not anymore.

523
00:43:01.635 --> 00:43:03.259
I don't like crowds.

524
00:43:04.925 --> 00:43:05.967
Me neither.

525
00:43:07.175 --> 00:43:09.342
Why not? They all love you now.

526
00:43:09.425 --> 00:43:11.009
You're the big hero.

527
00:43:12.175 --> 00:43:13.760
Don't like heroes.

528
00:43:15.717 --> 00:43:19.175
It must have felt good sticking
a knife in that horned fucker.

529
00:43:20.467 --> 00:43:22.175
Felt better than dying.

530
00:43:25.635 --> 00:43:27.342
You're heading
to King's Landing?

531
00:43:28.635 --> 00:43:31.050
I have some
unfinished business.

532
00:43:32.384 --> 00:43:33.800
Me too.

533
00:43:39.885 --> 00:43:42.009
I don't plan on coming back.

534
00:43:44.384 --> 00:43:46.009
Neither do I.

535
00:43:47.635 --> 00:43:50.009
Gonna leave me to die again
if I get hurt?

536
00:43:52.342 --> 00:43:53.342
Probably.

537
00:44:37.550 --> 00:44:38.550
My lady.

538
00:44:42.800 --> 00:44:45.550
"My lord"
is the standard response.

539
00:44:47.967 --> 00:44:49.384
Why her?

540
00:44:53.425 --> 00:44:55.425
You know she loves your brother.

541
00:44:55.509 --> 00:44:57.635
That doesn't mean
she'll be a good queen.

542
00:44:58.842 --> 00:45:01.550
You seem determined
to dislike her.

543
00:45:03.009 --> 00:45:04.175
A good relationship

544
00:45:04.259 --> 00:45:05.652
between the Iron Throne
and the North

545
00:45:05.675 --> 00:45:07.425
has been the core
of every peaceful.

546
00:45:07.509 --> 00:45:09.092
prosperous reign
we've ever known.

547
00:45:09.175 --> 00:45:10.675
Jon will be
Warden of the North.

548
00:45:10.760 --> 00:45:12.760
so a good relationship
seems likely.

549
00:45:14.467 --> 00:45:17.675
I don't expect him to spend
much time here going forward.

550
00:45:17.760 --> 00:45:19.760
Well.
I suppose that's up to him.

551
00:45:24.092 --> 00:45:25.467
Sansa. look at me.

552
00:45:31.217 --> 00:45:33.384
With Jon in the capital.

553
00:45:33.467 --> 00:45:36.134
you'll be the true power
in the North.

554
00:45:36.217 --> 00:45:38.009
I'd feel much better
about the future

555
00:45:38.092 --> 00:45:39.425
if I left here today believing

556
00:45:39.509 --> 00:45:41.092
that you and Daenerys
were allies.

557
00:45:41.175 --> 00:45:44.925
What are you worried about?
Jon's taking our army with him.

558
00:45:45.009 --> 00:45:46.675
Your queen
still has her dragons...

559
00:45:46.760 --> 00:45:47.925
She's your queen too.

560
00:45:54.967 --> 00:45:57.217
You don't have to be her friend.

561
00:45:57.300 --> 00:45:59.217
But why provoke her?

562
00:45:59.300 --> 00:46:01.550
How is that in the best interest
of your family.

563
00:46:01.635 --> 00:46:04.050
- or the North. or...?
- You're afraid of her.

564
00:46:06.509 --> 00:46:10.842
Every good ruler
needs to inspire a bit of fear.

565
00:46:13.425 --> 00:46:15.717
I don't want Jon
to go down there.

566
00:46:15.800 --> 00:46:19.467
The men in my family
don't do well in the capital.

567
00:46:19.550 --> 00:46:22.259
No. but as your brother
once told me.

568
00:46:22.342 --> 00:46:23.717
he's not a Stark.

569
00:46:29.300 --> 00:46:30.675
Are you all right?

570
00:46:37.175 --> 00:46:39.760
Her people love her.
you've seen that.

571
00:46:39.842 --> 00:46:42.175
You've seen
how they fight for her.

572
00:46:42.259 --> 00:46:45.425
She wants to make the world
a better place.

573
00:46:47.760 --> 00:46:49.842
I believe in her.

574
00:47:04.717 --> 00:47:06.050
Tyrion.

575
00:47:08.885 --> 00:47:11.467
What if there's someone else?

576
00:47:11.550 --> 00:47:13.175
Someone better?

577
00:47:21.509 --> 00:47:23.550
You're not gonna
ride the dragon south?

578
00:47:27.259 --> 00:47:28.425
Just a horse.

579
00:47:29.760 --> 00:47:30.925
Rhaegal needs to heal.

580
00:47:31.009 --> 00:47:32.717
He doesn't need me
weighing him down.

581
00:47:32.800 --> 00:47:36.134
You weigh as much
as two fleas fucking.

582
00:47:37.425 --> 00:47:39.092
I'm taking the Free Folk home.

583
00:47:40.092 --> 00:47:42.842
We've had enough of the south.

584
00:47:42.925 --> 00:47:44.967
The women down here
don't like me.

585
00:47:47.050 --> 00:47:49.217
This is the North. you know.

586
00:47:50.467 --> 00:47:52.885
And the Free Folk
are welcome to stay.

587
00:47:54.425 --> 00:47:56.092
It isn't home.

588
00:47:56.175 --> 00:47:57.635
We need room to wander.

589
00:47:57.717 --> 00:47:59.800
I'll take them
back through Castle Black

590
00:47:59.885 --> 00:48:02.342
as soon as
the winter storms pass.

591
00:48:02.425 --> 00:48:04.092
Back where we belong.

592
00:48:08.050 --> 00:48:10.384
It's where he belongs too.

593
00:48:10.467 --> 00:48:13.175
A direwolf has no place
in the south.

594
00:48:14.425 --> 00:48:16.800
Will you take him with you?

595
00:48:18.050 --> 00:48:20.009
He'll be happier up there.

596
00:48:21.050 --> 00:48:22.342
So would you.

597
00:48:24.342 --> 00:48:26.760
I wish I was going with you.

598
00:48:31.134 --> 00:48:32.425
This is farewell. then.

599
00:48:34.009 --> 00:48:35.675
You never know.

600
00:48:41.885 --> 00:48:44.134
You've got the North in you.

601
00:48:45.635 --> 00:48:47.092
The real North.

602
00:49:19.592 --> 00:49:22.760
Yes. well. the nights
have been getting longer

603
00:49:22.842 --> 00:49:25.425
and there wasn't that much
to do in Oldtown.

604
00:49:25.509 --> 00:49:28.134
There's only so many books
a person can read. so we...

605
00:49:28.217 --> 00:49:30.925
I'm sure he knows
how it happens. Sam.

606
00:49:34.217 --> 00:49:36.885
If it's a boy.
we want to name him Jon.

607
00:49:40.217 --> 00:49:41.717
I hope it's a girl.

608
00:50:00.550 --> 00:50:02.675
You're the best friend
I ever had.

609
00:50:05.134 --> 00:50:07.175
You too. Sam.

610
00:51:07.717 --> 00:51:10.009
Think of the past 20 years.

611
00:51:11.009 --> 00:51:13.925
The war. the murder. the misery.

612
00:51:14.009 --> 00:51:16.425
All of it because
Robert Baratheon loved someone

613
00:51:16.509 --> 00:51:18.425
who didn't love him back.

614
00:51:20.509 --> 00:51:21.675
How many others know?

615
00:51:23.467 --> 00:51:26.092
Including us? Eight.

616
00:51:26.175 --> 00:51:28.259
Well. then
it's not a secret anymore.

617
00:51:28.342 --> 00:51:30.134
It's information.

618
00:51:30.217 --> 00:51:33.550
If a handful of people know now.
hundreds will know soon.

619
00:51:33.635 --> 00:51:35.050
Then what happens?

620
00:51:35.134 --> 00:51:36.717
She loses the North.

621
00:51:36.800 --> 00:51:39.592
She loses the Vale.
Sansa will make sure of that.

622
00:51:39.675 --> 00:51:41.092
No. it's worse than that.

623
00:51:41.175 --> 00:51:43.925
He has the better claim
to the throne.

624
00:51:44.009 --> 00:51:46.217
He doesn't want the throne.

625
00:51:46.300 --> 00:51:48.717
I'm not sure it matters
what he wants.

626
00:51:49.925 --> 00:51:53.175
The fact is.
people are drawn to him.

627
00:51:53.259 --> 00:51:54.967
Wildlings. Northmen.

628
00:51:56.967 --> 00:51:58.217
He's a war hero.

629
00:52:02.675 --> 00:52:04.842
He loves our queen.

630
00:52:06.384 --> 00:52:07.675
And she loves him.

631
00:52:09.885 --> 00:52:12.300
If we marry them.
they could rule together.

632
00:52:13.342 --> 00:52:14.509
She's his aunt.

633
00:52:14.592 --> 00:52:15.985
That never stopped
a Targaryen before.

634
00:52:16.009 --> 00:52:17.717
No. but Jon grew up
in Winterfell.

635
00:52:17.800 --> 00:52:20.050
Is marrying your aunt
common in the North?

636
00:52:22.800 --> 00:52:24.467
You know our queen
better than I do.

637
00:52:24.550 --> 00:52:27.259
Do you think
she wants to share the throne?

638
00:52:27.342 --> 00:52:29.885
She does not like to have
her authority questioned.

639
00:52:29.967 --> 00:52:31.217
Something she has in common

640
00:52:31.300 --> 00:52:33.885
with every monarch
who ever lived.

641
00:52:33.967 --> 00:52:35.760
I worry about her state of mind.

642
00:52:35.842 --> 00:52:37.967
We are advisors to the queen.

643
00:52:38.050 --> 00:52:41.384
Worrying about her state of mind
is our job.

644
00:52:49.342 --> 00:52:51.384
We still have to take
King's Landing.

645
00:52:52.550 --> 00:52:55.134
Maybe Cersei will win
and kill us all.

646
00:52:55.217 --> 00:52:57.509
That would solve our problems.

647
00:55:01.050 --> 00:55:03.509
Get to the skiff. Now!

648
00:55:05.592 --> 00:55:07.050
Spears!

649
00:55:07.134 --> 00:55:09.092
They're coming round again!

650
00:55:17.717 --> 00:55:19.175
Go!

651
00:55:19.259 --> 00:55:20.467
Clear!

652
00:55:20.550 --> 00:55:22.425
Man your stations!

653
00:55:22.509 --> 00:55:24.175
No!

654
00:55:42.092 --> 00:55:44.675
- Go! Go!
- Clear!

655
00:56:20.384 --> 00:56:21.467
Missandei?

656
00:56:23.050 --> 00:56:24.300
Missandei!

657
00:56:30.384 --> 00:56:31.800
Missandei!

658
00:56:36.717 --> 00:56:38.717
Our message was well-received. then?

659
00:56:38.800 --> 00:56:42.092
Your people have
heard the Usurper is coming.

660
00:56:42.175 --> 00:56:44.675
They are grateful
for your protection

661
00:56:44.760 --> 00:56:47.134
within the walls
of the Red Keep.

662
00:56:49.384 --> 00:56:51.342
You're certain about the dragon?

663
00:56:51.425 --> 00:56:53.675
I saw it sink beneath the waves.

664
00:56:53.760 --> 00:56:56.009
That must have been glorious.

665
00:56:58.217 --> 00:57:00.342
The glory is yours. my queen.

666
00:57:01.842 --> 00:57:04.342
When the war is won.
the Lion shall rule the land.

667
00:57:04.425 --> 00:57:06.092
the Kraken shall rule the sea...

668
00:57:07.467 --> 00:57:10.675
and our child
shall one day rule them all.

669
00:57:27.509 --> 00:57:29.217
She's coming for you.

670
00:57:30.342 --> 00:57:31.550
Of course she is.

671
00:57:34.342 --> 00:57:36.050
Keep the gates open.

672
00:57:36.134 --> 00:57:38.760
If she wants to take the castle.
she'll have to murder

673
00:57:38.842 --> 00:57:41.342
thousands
of innocent people first.

674
00:57:47.425 --> 00:57:49.925
So much for
"the Breaker of Chains."

675
00:58:03.467 --> 00:58:05.925
We will storm the city. my queen.

676
00:58:06.009 --> 00:58:09.217
We will kill your enemies.
All of them.

677
00:58:09.300 --> 00:58:10.384
Your Grace.

678
00:58:11.967 --> 00:58:15.635
I promised you I would look you
in the eye and speak directly

679
00:58:15.717 --> 00:58:18.050
if I ever thought
you were making a mistake.

680
00:58:21.592 --> 00:58:24.342
This is a mistake.

681
00:58:26.885 --> 00:58:29.425
You saw my child
fall from the sky.

682
00:58:31.050 --> 00:58:33.050
They took Missandei.

683
00:58:33.134 --> 00:58:35.134
Cersei needs to be destroyed.

684
00:58:35.217 --> 00:58:39.425
but if we attack King's Landing
with Drogon and the Unsullied

685
00:58:39.509 --> 00:58:40.717
and the Dothraki.

686
00:58:40.800 --> 00:58:42.967
tens of thousands
of innocents will die.

687
00:58:43.050 --> 00:58:47.760
That is why Cersei is bringing
them into the Red Keep.

688
00:58:47.842 --> 00:58:51.509
These are the people
you came here to protect.

689
00:58:51.592 --> 00:58:53.217
I beg you. Your Grace.

690
00:58:53.300 --> 00:58:57.009
Do not destroy the city
you came to save.

691
00:58:57.092 --> 00:59:00.925
Do not become what you
have always struggled to defeat.

692
00:59:05.760 --> 00:59:08.800
Do you believe we're here
for a reason. Lord Varys?

693
00:59:12.259 --> 00:59:15.342
I'm here to free the world
from tyrants.

694
00:59:16.509 --> 00:59:17.967
That is my destiny...

695
00:59:19.300 --> 00:59:22.259
and I will serve it.
no matter the cost.

696
00:59:29.217 --> 00:59:32.050
It could be a fortnight before
Jon and the allied armies

697
00:59:32.134 --> 00:59:34.134
make it to King's Landing.

698
00:59:34.217 --> 00:59:37.050
In the meantime.
demand Cersei surrender.

699
00:59:37.134 --> 00:59:40.467
Offer her her life
in exchange for the throne.

700
00:59:42.009 --> 00:59:44.509
If there's a chance
to avoid the coming slaughter.

701
00:59:44.592 --> 00:59:47.009
we should make the effort.

702
00:59:47.092 --> 00:59:49.967
Speaking to Cersei
will not prevent a slaughter.

703
00:59:52.217 --> 00:59:53.800
But perhaps it's good
the people see

704
00:59:53.885 --> 00:59:57.885
that Daenerys Stormborn made
every effort to avoid bloodshed.

705
00:59:57.967 --> 01:00:00.300
and Cersei Lannister refused.

706
01:00:02.009 --> 01:00:03.425
They should know whom to blame

707
01:00:03.509 --> 01:00:05.635
when the sky
falls down upon them.

708
01:00:19.800 --> 01:00:22.384
I've served tyrants
most of my life.

709
01:00:23.384 --> 01:00:26.592
They all talk about destiny.

710
01:00:26.675 --> 01:00:29.925
She's a girl who walked
into a fire with three stones

711
01:00:30.009 --> 01:00:32.675
and walked out
with three dragons.

712
01:00:32.760 --> 01:00:35.509
How could she not
believe in destiny?

713
01:00:35.592 --> 01:00:37.467
Perhaps that's the problem.

714
01:00:37.550 --> 01:00:38.760
Her life has convinced her

715
01:00:38.842 --> 01:00:40.717
that she was sent here
to save us all.

716
01:00:40.800 --> 01:00:42.717
And how do you know she wasn't?

717
01:00:44.967 --> 01:00:46.885
Then there's the problem
of Jon Snow.

718
01:00:53.384 --> 01:00:56.175
Perhaps
it's actually a solution.

719
01:00:57.717 --> 01:00:59.134
You know them both.

720
01:00:59.217 --> 01:01:02.342
Tell me. who do you think
would make a better ruler?

721
01:01:07.635 --> 01:01:09.384
He doesn't want the throne.

722
01:01:09.467 --> 01:01:11.925
That's why he bent the knee.

723
01:01:12.009 --> 01:01:14.092
Have you considered
the best ruler

724
01:01:14.175 --> 01:01:16.592
might be someone
who doesn't want to rule?

725
01:01:16.675 --> 01:01:18.967
We're discussing treason.

726
01:01:19.050 --> 01:01:21.717
Don't pretend
you haven't thought about it.

727
01:01:21.800 --> 01:01:25.134
Of course I've thought about it.
Thoughts aren't treason.

728
01:01:27.217 --> 01:01:31.259
He's temperate and measured.
He's a man.

729
01:01:31.342 --> 01:01:34.092
which makes him more appealing
to the lords of Westeros.

730
01:01:34.175 --> 01:01:36.425
whose support
we are going to need.

731
01:01:36.509 --> 01:01:37.925
Joffrey was a man.

732
01:01:38.009 --> 01:01:40.259
I don't think a cock
is a true qualification.

733
01:01:40.342 --> 01:01:41.467
as I'm sure you'd agree.

734
01:01:41.550 --> 01:01:43.509
And he's the heir to the throne.

735
01:01:43.592 --> 01:01:47.592
Yes. because he's a man.
Cocks are important. I'm afraid.

736
01:01:50.467 --> 01:01:53.509
What about my earlier proposal?

737
01:01:53.592 --> 01:01:55.800
They could rule together
as king and queen.

738
01:01:57.425 --> 01:01:59.760
She's too strong for him.

739
01:01:59.842 --> 01:02:03.384
She'd bend him to her will.
as she already has.

740
01:02:03.467 --> 01:02:06.550
He could temper
her worst impulses.

741
01:02:06.635 --> 01:02:08.592
As you have?

742
01:02:11.675 --> 01:02:13.842
You're drinking quite a lot.

743
01:02:16.259 --> 01:02:19.885
A Targaryen father
and a Stark mother.

744
01:02:19.967 --> 01:02:22.885
Jon's the one man alive
who might actually be able

745
01:02:22.967 --> 01:02:24.842
to keep the North
in the Seven Kingdoms.

746
01:02:24.925 --> 01:02:26.565
How many kings and queens
have you served?

747
01:02:26.592 --> 01:02:27.967
Five? Six? I've lost count.

748
01:02:28.050 --> 01:02:29.902
- You've always known my reasons.
- At a certain point.

749
01:02:29.925 --> 01:02:31.550
you choose a person
you believe in.

750
01:02:31.635 --> 01:02:33.134
and you fight for that person.

751
01:02:33.217 --> 01:02:35.300
Even if you know it's a mistake?

752
01:02:37.134 --> 01:02:38.842
I believe in our queen.

753
01:02:41.384 --> 01:02:43.592
She'll make the right choice.

754
01:02:45.175 --> 01:02:48.050
With the help
of her loyal advisors.

755
01:02:51.800 --> 01:02:54.175
You know
where my loyalty stands.

756
01:02:54.259 --> 01:02:56.550
You know I will never
betray the realm.

757
01:02:56.635 --> 01:02:57.925
What is the realm?

758
01:02:58.009 --> 01:03:00.134
A vast continent.
home to millions of people.

759
01:03:00.217 --> 01:03:02.235
most of whom don't care
who sits on the Iron Throne.

760
01:03:02.259 --> 01:03:04.217
Millions of people.
many of whom will die

761
01:03:04.300 --> 01:03:06.967
if the wrong person
sits on that throne.

762
01:03:07.050 --> 01:03:08.259
We don't know their names.

763
01:03:08.342 --> 01:03:10.217
but they're just as real
as you and I.

764
01:03:10.300 --> 01:03:11.509
They deserve to live.

765
01:03:11.592 --> 01:03:13.509
They deserve
food for their children.

766
01:03:17.259 --> 01:03:21.550
I will act in their interest.
no matter the personal cost.

767
01:03:23.675 --> 01:03:26.342
So. what happens to her?

768
01:03:34.300 --> 01:03:35.509
Please.

769
01:03:37.800 --> 01:03:38.885
Don't.

770
01:03:43.550 --> 01:03:46.050
I've spoken
as honestly as I can.

771
01:03:47.550 --> 01:03:50.259
Each of us has a choice to make.

772
01:03:51.300 --> 01:03:54.259
I pray we choose wisely.

773
01:04:05.175 --> 01:04:07.009
I'm just about to start it.

774
01:04:07.092 --> 01:04:08.509
Good luck.

775
01:04:08.592 --> 01:04:10.509
Protect shell right up to the wall.

776
01:04:10.592 --> 01:04:12.235
All right.
I'll put another one on it.

777
01:04:12.259 --> 01:04:14.092
He's headed down to the cellar.

778
01:04:14.175 --> 01:04:16.217
I'll need a cart over here.

779
01:04:16.300 --> 01:04:17.509
That's it. thanks.

780
01:04:17.592 --> 01:04:19.175
Thank you.

781
01:04:19.259 --> 01:04:20.652
It's really heavy. mind you.

782
01:04:20.675 --> 01:04:21.925
We need some more water.

783
01:04:22.009 --> 01:04:23.592
Take it down there!

784
01:04:28.509 --> 01:04:30.925
...as are the rest
of her advisors.

785
01:04:33.259 --> 01:04:34.300
What happened?

786
01:04:39.925 --> 01:04:44.300
Euron Greyjoy ambushed
Queen Daenerys and her fleet.

787
01:04:44.384 --> 01:04:47.342
One of the dragons was killed.
several ships destroyed.

788
01:04:47.425 --> 01:04:49.592
Missandei captured.

789
01:04:51.467 --> 01:04:55.635
I always wanted to be there
when they execute your sister.

790
01:04:55.717 --> 01:04:58.425
Seems like
I won't get the chance.

791
01:06:05.175 --> 01:06:07.800
They're going to destroy
that city.

792
01:06:08.842 --> 01:06:10.342
You know they will.

793
01:06:10.425 --> 01:06:12.717
Have you ever run away from a fight?

794
01:06:14.675 --> 01:06:17.092
You're not like your sister.
You're not.

795
01:06:17.175 --> 01:06:19.300
You're better than she is.

796
01:06:19.384 --> 01:06:21.925
You're a good man
and you can't save her.

797
01:06:22.009 --> 01:06:23.925
You don't need to die with her.

798
01:06:24.009 --> 01:06:25.550
Stay here.

799
01:06:27.425 --> 01:06:28.760
Stay with me.

800
01:06:30.467 --> 01:06:32.425
Please.

801
01:06:33.509 --> 01:06:34.509
Stay.

802
01:06:41.175 --> 01:06:43.009
You think I'm a good man?

803
01:06:47.760 --> 01:06:50.467
I pushed a boy
out a tower window.

804
01:06:50.550 --> 01:06:52.635
crippled him for life

805
01:06:52.717 --> 01:06:53.717
for Cersei.

806
01:06:56.800 --> 01:06:59.760
I strangled my cousin
with my own hands

807
01:07:00.760 --> 01:07:02.885
just to get back to Cersei.

808
01:07:05.885 --> 01:07:07.217
I would have murdered

809
01:07:07.300 --> 01:07:11.509
every man. woman and child
in Riverrun

810
01:07:11.592 --> 01:07:12.717
for Cersei.

811
01:07:21.592 --> 01:07:23.425
She's hateful.

812
01:07:25.300 --> 01:07:26.550
And so am I.

813
01:10:01.635 --> 01:10:02.635
My lord.

814
01:10:05.926 --> 01:10:08.966
Queen Daenerys demands Cersei's
unconditional surrender

815
01:10:09.051 --> 01:10:11.760
and the immediate release
of Missandei of Naath.

816
01:10:13.426 --> 01:10:17.842
Queen Cersei demands Daenerys's
unconditional surrender.

817
01:10:17.926 --> 01:10:21.966
If she refuses. Missandei
of Naath will die here and now.

818
01:10:23.635 --> 01:10:24.635
Qyburn...

819
01:10:26.091 --> 01:10:27.885
you're a rational man.

820
01:10:27.966 --> 01:10:30.926
Or so I flatter myself.
my lord.

821
01:10:31.009 --> 01:10:32.467
We have a chance here.

822
01:10:33.717 --> 01:10:37.216
perhaps our last chance.
to avoid carnage.

823
01:10:37.301 --> 01:10:38.301
Yes.

824
01:10:40.051 --> 01:10:41.051
Help me.

825
01:10:42.216 --> 01:10:45.091
I don't want to see
this city burn.

826
01:10:45.176 --> 01:10:48.467
I don't want to hear the screams
of children burning alive.

827
01:10:50.467 --> 01:10:53.426
No. it is not a pleasant sound.

828
01:10:55.635 --> 01:10:57.801
I... I don't want to hear it.

829
01:10:58.801 --> 01:11:00.301
Help me save this city.

830
01:11:02.259 --> 01:11:04.926
My lord. I am only a mouthpiece
for our queen.

831
01:11:05.009 --> 01:11:06.717
Your queen.

832
01:11:06.801 --> 01:11:08.926
Cersei is
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

833
01:11:09.009 --> 01:11:10.134
You are her subject.

834
01:11:10.216 --> 01:11:12.259
Her reign is over.

835
01:11:12.342 --> 01:11:14.885
You understand this.
Help her understand it.

836
01:11:14.966 --> 01:11:17.509
We understand
nothing of the sort.

837
01:11:18.842 --> 01:11:21.384
Your queen's last dragon
is vulnerable.

838
01:11:21.467 --> 01:11:24.384
Your armies
are battle-weary and depleted.

839
01:11:24.467 --> 01:11:27.760
while ours have been reinforced
with the Golden Compan...

840
01:11:45.635 --> 01:11:47.801
Ready!

841
01:11:47.885 --> 01:11:48.926
Nock!

842
01:11:51.801 --> 01:11:53.009
Draw!

843
01:12:59.301 --> 01:13:02.134
I know you don't care
about your people.

844
01:13:04.091 --> 01:13:05.885
Why should you?

845
01:13:07.384 --> 01:13:10.966
They hate you and you hate them.

846
01:13:16.467 --> 01:13:18.926
But you're not a monster.

847
01:13:20.966 --> 01:13:22.176
I know this.

848
01:13:24.301 --> 01:13:27.134
I know this
because I've seen it.

849
01:13:31.009 --> 01:13:33.467
You've always
loved your children.

850
01:13:35.467 --> 01:13:36.966
More than yourself.

851
01:13:37.966 --> 01:13:39.426
more than Jaime...

852
01:13:42.216 --> 01:13:43.676
more than anything.

853
01:13:46.635 --> 01:13:48.301
I beg you.

854
01:13:50.509 --> 01:13:53.966
If not for yourself.
then for your child.

855
01:13:57.509 --> 01:14:00.051
Your reign is over.

856
01:14:00.134 --> 01:14:03.134
but that doesn't mean
your life has to end.

857
01:14:06.009 --> 01:14:08.885
It doesn't mean
your baby has to die.

858
01:14:56.717 --> 01:15:00.384
If you have any last words.
now is the time.

859
01:15:25.134 --> 01:15:26.426
Dracarys.

860
01:15:35.635 --> 01:15:37.259
No.

861
